"{\"uid\": \"newstatesman.com-comment-2024-07-the-spectre-of-the-olympics\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Reviewing politicsand culture since 1913 As London 2012 showed, the Games have the power to change a city - for better or for worse.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 133, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 45, \"end\": 56, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6752935379609854e-22, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"politicsand culture\", \"from\": 10, \"to\": 29}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 64, \"to\": 73}, {\"ngram\": \"the power\", \"from\": 79, \"to\": 88}, {\"ngram\": \"a city\", \"from\": 99, \"to\": 105}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ByClive Martin Yesterday evening saw the start of the Paris Olympics, with a slightly mad opening ceremony which probably asked more questions than it answered.\", \"from\": 135, \"to\": 296, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 143, \"end\": 149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\", \"score\": 0.9999926235895266, \"rank\": 7.376454363450465e-06, \"text\": \"Martin\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the start\", \"from\": 172, \"to\": 181}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 185, \"to\": 203}, {\"ngram\": \"a slightly mad opening ceremony\", \"from\": 210, \"to\": 241}, {\"ngram\": \"more questions\", \"from\": 263, \"to\": 277}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the Games themselves are at least now underway, and while it may be easy to forget with all those badminton heats and 10-metre air rifle bouts sitting behind the red button, today also marks exactly 12 years since the London 2012 opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 297, \"to\": 548, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 519, \"end\": 547, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics_opening_ceremony\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"London 2012 opening ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics_opening_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics_opening_ceremony\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 301, \"to\": 310}, {\"ngram\": \"10-metre air rifle bouts\", \"from\": 419, \"to\": 443}, {\"ngram\": \"the red button\", \"from\": 459, \"to\": 473}, {\"ngram\": \"today\", \"from\": 475, \"to\": 480}, {\"ngram\": \"exactly 12 years\", \"from\": 492, \"to\": 508}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With only Rio and the Covid-riddled Tokyo games to split them apart, London was the last time a European nation had to make such a grand cultural address to the world - trying to present and define its essence even as it was bogged down in its own political-social upheavals.\", \"from\": 549, \"to\": 824, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 559, \"end\": 562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 0.9999988088391365, \"rank\": 1.1911625687074958e-06, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}, {\"begin\": 585, \"end\": 590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_Station\", \"score\": 0.7229728996426259, \"rank\": 0.31006253359095953, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_Station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_Station\"}, {\"begin\": 618, \"end\": 624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999979099812, \"rank\": 2.0903602504530897e-09, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the last time\", \"from\": 629, \"to\": 642}, {\"ngram\": \"a European nation\", \"from\": 643, \"to\": 660}, {\"ngram\": \"such a grand cultural address\", \"from\": 673, \"to\": 702}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 706, \"to\": 715}, {\"ngram\": \"its essence\", \"from\": 747, \"to\": 758}, {\"ngram\": \"its own political-social upheavals\", \"from\": 789, \"to\": 823}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 2012 ceremony now stands closer in time to the launch of Millennium Dome than the present day.\", \"from\": 826, \"to\": 924, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The 2012 ceremony\", \"from\": 826, \"to\": 843}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 865, \"to\": 869}, {\"ngram\": \"the launch\", \"from\": 873, \"to\": 883}, {\"ngram\": \"Millennium Dome\", \"from\": 887, \"to\": 902}, {\"ngram\": \"the present day\", \"from\": 908, \"to\": 923}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That should really be one of those staggering, slightly depressing markers of time - like the first Strokes album being older than Bukayo Saka, orDragons' Denturning 20 next year.\", \"from\": 925, \"to\": 1104, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1056, \"end\": 1067, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bukayo_Saka\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bukayo Saka\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bukayo_Saka\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bukayo_Saka\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"those staggering, slightly depressing markers\", \"from\": 954, \"to\": 999}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 1003, \"to\": 1007}, {\"ngram\": \"the first Strokes album\", \"from\": 1015, \"to\": 1038}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It should induce a pang of impermanence and mortality, and yet it does not really.\", \"from\": 1105, \"to\": 1187, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a pang\", \"from\": 1122, \"to\": 1128}, {\"ngram\": \"impermanence\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1144}, {\"ngram\": \"mortality\", \"from\": 1149, \"to\": 1158}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Because in many ways, London 2012 feels even longer ago, and increasingly like a false memory - one melded together from bits of Adam Curtis b-roll and snippets of reality.\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1360, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1210, \"end\": 1221, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6752935379609854e-22, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1317, \"end\": 1328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Curtis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Curtis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Curtis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Curtis\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"many ways\", \"from\": 1199, \"to\": 1208}, {\"ngram\": \"a false memory\", \"from\": 1267, \"to\": 1281}, {\"ngram\": \"one\", \"from\": 1284, \"to\": 1287}, {\"ngram\": \"bits\", \"from\": 1309, \"to\": 1313}, {\"ngram\": \"snippets\", \"from\": 1340, \"to\": 1348}, {\"ngram\": \"reality\", \"from\": 1352, \"to\": 1359}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Did Frank Turner really play on a giant grass mound inside the stadium?\", \"from\": 1361, \"to\": 1432, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1365, \"end\": 1377, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frank_Turner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6997625795230037e-45, \"text\": \"Frank Turner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frank_Turner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frank_Turner\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a giant grass mound\", \"from\": 1393, \"to\": 1412}, {\"ngram\": \"the stadium\", \"from\": 1420, \"to\": 1431}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Did Kenneth Branagh dress up as Isambard Kingdom Brunel or are we making it up?\", \"from\": 1433, \"to\": 1512, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1437, \"end\": 1452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenneth_Branagh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kenneth Branagh\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenneth_Branagh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenneth_Branagh\"}, {\"begin\": 1482, \"end\": 1488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isambard_Kingdom_Brunel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6716568456516995e-17, \"text\": \"Brunel\", \"types\": [\"Q81096\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isambard_Kingdom_Brunel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isambard_Kingdom_Brunel\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Was Mr Bean there, or did we all experience some national norovirus dream?\", \"from\": 1513, \"to\": 1587, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1517, \"end\": 1524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mr._Bean\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.189594591960767e-45, \"text\": \"Mr Bean\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mr._Bean\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mr._Bean\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some national norovirus dream\", \"from\": 1557, \"to\": 1586}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are all manner of unreal moments to pore over now: David Beckham bombing under Tower Bridge in a speedboat; Bradley Wiggins sitting upon an ornate throne in the grounds of Hampton Court Palace; the current King doing the \\\"mobot\\\"; the strange omnipresence of Dizzee Rascal's \\\"Bonkers\\\".\", \"from\": 1589, \"to\": 1879, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1646, \"end\": 1659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Beckham\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"David Beckham\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Beckham\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Beckham\"}, {\"begin\": 1703, \"end\": 1718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bradley_Wiggins\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bradley Wiggins\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bradley_Wiggins\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bradley_Wiggins\"}, {\"begin\": 1767, \"end\": 1774, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Hampton\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.95847426365138e-23, \"text\": \"Hampton\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Hampton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Hampton\"}, {\"begin\": 1801, \"end\": 1805, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monarch\", \"score\": 0.8291511044426716, \"rank\": 0.20605248160109807, \"text\": \"King\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monarch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monarch\"}, {\"begin\": 1853, \"end\": 1866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dizzee_Rascal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dizzee Rascal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dizzee_Rascal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dizzee_Rascal\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"manner\", \"from\": 1603, \"to\": 1609}, {\"ngram\": \"unreal moments\", \"from\": 1613, \"to\": 1627}, {\"ngram\": \"Tower Bridge\", \"from\": 1674, \"to\": 1686}, {\"ngram\": \"a speedboat\", \"from\": 1690, \"to\": 1701}, {\"ngram\": \"an ornate throne\", \"from\": 1732, \"to\": 1748}, {\"ngram\": \"the grounds\", \"from\": 1752, \"to\": 1763}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"mobot\", \"from\": 1812, \"to\": 1822}, {\"ngram\": \"the strange omnipresence\", \"from\": 1825, \"to\": 1849}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It appears in the collective mind not as a sporting triumph, but like some CCP soap opera.\", \"from\": 1880, \"to\": 1970, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1955, \"end\": 1958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Communist_Party\", \"score\": 0.9462556320675736, \"rank\": 0.05679685979898819, \"text\": \"CCP\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Communist_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Communist_Party\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the collective mind\", \"from\": 1894, \"to\": 1913}, {\"ngram\": \"a sporting triumph\", \"from\": 1921, \"to\": 1939}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A flash-sequence of heavy branding and light jingoism - and all featuring a cast of characters doomed to varying fates.\", \"from\": 1971, \"to\": 2090, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A flash-sequence\", \"from\": 1971, \"to\": 1987}, {\"ngram\": \"heavy branding and light jingoism\", \"from\": 1991, \"to\": 2024}, {\"ngram\": \"a cast\", \"from\": 2045, \"to\": 2051}, {\"ngram\": \"characters\", \"from\": 2055, \"to\": 2065}, {\"ngram\": \"varying fates\", \"from\": 2076, \"to\": 2089}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some have fallen far: even as exalted names as Bradley Wiggins and Mo Farah have become partially shrouded in both controversy and tragedy.\", \"from\": 2092, \"to\": 2231, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2139, \"end\": 2154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bradley_Wiggins\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bradley Wiggins\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bradley_Wiggins\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bradley_Wiggins\"}, {\"begin\": 2159, \"end\": 2167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mo_Farah\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mo Farah\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mo_Farah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mo_Farah\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"exalted names\", \"from\": 2122, \"to\": 2135}, {\"ngram\": \"both controversy\", \"from\": 2202, \"to\": 2218}, {\"ngram\": \"tragedy\", \"from\": 2223, \"to\": 2230}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But as the 2012 generation withers and decays - witness Andy Murray entering the Paris Olympics like an old police horse receiving a medal - it is striking to observe that the effects of those last British Olympics are still playing out in London.\", \"from\": 2232, \"to\": 2479, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2288, \"end\": 2299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.328800366858302e-43, \"text\": \"Andy Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 2472, \"end\": 2478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999979099812, \"rank\": 2.0903602504530897e-09, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 2012 generation withers\", \"from\": 2239, \"to\": 2266}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 2309, \"to\": 2327}, {\"ngram\": \"an old police horse\", \"from\": 2333, \"to\": 2352}, {\"ngram\": \"a medal\", \"from\": 2363, \"to\": 2370}, {\"ngram\": \"the effects\", \"from\": 2404, \"to\": 2415}, {\"ngram\": \"those last British Olympics\", \"from\": 2419, \"to\": 2446}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Who knows whether Paris 2024 will ultimately be seen as a catalyst for progress, or an event that turns over the rock to reveal all of Paris's own iniquities and dysfunction (the travel chaos of the last 24 hours might suggest the latter).\", \"from\": 2480, \"to\": 2719, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2498, \"end\": 2508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.434062245726339e-24, \"t