"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.531686910764791e-24, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2881, \"end\": 2887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999302875247336, \"rank\": 6.917748485418369e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2900, \"end\": 2906, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999979099812, \"rank\": 2.0903602504530897e-09, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 2911, \"end\": 2918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999978599985458, \"rank\": 2.1386970618953864e-06, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some locust years\", \"from\": 2942, \"to\": 2959}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A carnival like the Olympics felt rather out of place.\", \"from\": 2971, \"to\": 3025, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A carnival\", \"from\": 2971, \"to\": 2981}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2987, \"to\": 2999}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 3019, \"to\": 3024}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps it made sense when the bid went in, in some fit of New Labour 25-year-plan optimism, but in the wake of austerity, the riots, oscillating terror threats and a financial crisis, London seemed a slightly odd place for it to land.\", \"from\": 3026, \"to\": 3261, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3211, \"end\": 3217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999979099812, \"rank\": 2.0903602504530897e-09, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sense\", \"from\": 3042, \"to\": 3047}, {\"ngram\": \"the bid\", \"from\": 3053, \"to\": 3060}, {\"ngram\": \"some fit\", \"from\": 3073, \"to\": 3081}, {\"ngram\": \"New Labour 25-year-plan optimism\", \"from\": 3085, \"to\": 3117}, {\"ngram\": \"the wake\", \"from\": 3126, \"to\": 3134}, {\"ngram\": \"austerity\", \"from\": 3138, \"to\": 3147}, {\"ngram\": \"the riots\", \"from\": 3149, \"to\": 3158}, {\"ngram\": \"terror threats\", \"from\": 3172, \"to\": 3186}, {\"ngram\": \"a financial crisis\", \"from\": 3191, \"to\": 3209}, {\"ngram\": \"a slightly odd place\", \"from\": 3225, \"to\": 3245}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But, while the medals and the names are fading from memory, the Olympics both framed and shaped a turning point for London in particular.\", \"from\": 3262, \"to\": 3399, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3378, \"end\": 3384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999979099812, \"rank\": 2.0903602504530897e-09, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the medals\", \"from\": 3273, \"to\": 3283}, {\"ngram\": \"the names\", \"from\": 3288, \"to\": 3297}, {\"ngram\": \"memory\", \"from\": 3314, \"to\": 3320}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3322, \"to\": 3334}, {\"ngram\": \"a turning point\", \"from\": 3358, \"to\": 3373}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although they were not the only factor, they helped shape the city into the boundless, iridescent, streamlined metropolis it is today.\", \"from\": 3400, \"to\": 3534, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the only factor\", \"from\": 3423, \"to\": 3438}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 3458, \"to\": 3466}, {\"ngram\": \"the boundless, iridescent\", \"from\": 3472, \"to\": 3497}, {\"ngram\": \"streamlined metropolis\", \"from\": 3499, \"to\": 3521}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In early 2012, the capital was in a state of perpetual metamorphosis.\", \"from\": 3538, \"to\": 3607, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the capital\", \"from\": 3553, \"to\": 3564}, {\"ngram\": \"a state\", \"from\": 3572, \"to\": 3579}, {\"ngram\": \"perpetual metamorphosis\", \"from\": 3583, \"to\": 3606}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the time, I was living and working in East London, staying in a squat protection scheme in the shadow of Silicon Roundabout (another one of David Cameron's questionable legacy projects).\", \"from\": 3608, \"to\": 3797, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3716, \"end\": 3734, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_London_Tech_City\", \"score\": 0.9999999990750439, \"rank\": 9.252724900156606e-10, \"text\": \"Silicon Roundabout\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_London_Tech_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_London_Tech_City\"}, {\"begin\": 3751, \"end\": 3764, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Cameron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6578235661814552e-30, \"text\": \"David Cameron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Cameron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Cameron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 3611, \"to\": 3619}, {\"ngram\": \"East London\", \"from\": 3649, \"to\": 3660}, {\"ngram\": \"a squat protection scheme\", \"from\": 3673, \"to\": 3698}, {\"ngram\": \"the shadow\", \"from\": 3702, \"to\": 3712}]}, {\"sentence\": \"My rent was \\u00a3250 a month, and that seemed to make perfect sense.\", \"from\": 3798, \"to\": 3862, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"My rent\", \"from\": 3798, \"to\": 3805}, {\"ngram\": \"perfect sense\", \"from\": 3848, \"to\": 3861}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There were parties every night of the week, grand new ventures opening up, and a shared belief that you were in the thick of some great boom.\", \"from\": 3863, \"to\": 4004, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"parties\", \"from\": 3874, \"to\": 3881}, {\"ngram\": \"the week\", \"from\": 3897, \"to\": 3905}, {\"ngram\": \"the thick\", \"from\": 3975, \"to\": 3984}, {\"ngram\": \"some great boom\", \"from\": 3988, \"to\": 4003}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There were cranes all over the skyline, plans to raze every old primary school and Sixties office block in sight, and an understanding that the nature of work and media and wealth was about to be shunted into the future.\", \"from\": 4005, \"to\": 4225, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"cranes\", \"from\": 4016, \"to\": 4022}, {\"ngram\": \"the skyline\", \"from\": 4032, \"to\": 4043}, {\"ngram\": \"every old primary school and Sixties office block\", \"from\": 4059, \"to\": 4108}, {\"ngram\": \"sight\", \"from\": 4112, \"to\": 4117}, {\"ngram\": \"an understanding\", \"from\": 4123, \"to\": 4139}, {\"ngram\": \"work\", \"from\": 4159, \"to\": 4163}, {\"ngram\": \"media\", \"from\": 4168, \"to\": 4173}, {\"ngram\": \"wealth\", \"from\": 4178, \"to\": 4184}, {\"ngram\": \"the future\", \"from\": 4214, \"to\": 4224}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Due to massive amounts of tech investment, and digital media companies flooding the area, the City of London started to look rather old hat - almost like it were Billingsgate or Smithfield, a quaint relic from the old town.\", \"from\": 4227, \"to\": 4450, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"massive amounts\", \"from\": 4234, \"to\": 4249}, {\"ngram\": \"tech investment\", \"from\": 4253, \"to\": 4268}, {\"ngram\": \"digital media companies\", \"from\": 4274, \"to\": 4297}, {\"ngram\": \"the area\", \"from\": 4307, \"to\": 4315}, {\"ngram\": \"the City\", \"from\": 4317, \"to\": 4325}, {\"ngram\": \"London\", \"from\": 4329, \"to\": 4335}, {\"ngram\": \"rather old hat\", \"from\": 4352, \"to\": 4366}, {\"ngram\": \"a quaint relic\", \"from\": 4417, \"to\": 4431}, {\"ngram\": \"the old town\", \"from\": 4437, \"to\": 4449}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Like a new generation of yuppies, we had been told it was Facebook ads that would make us millionaires, and for some reason we believed it.\", \"from\": 4451, \"to\": 4590, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a new generation\", \"from\": 4456, \"to\": 4472}, {\"ngram\": \"yuppies\", \"from\": 4476, \"to\": 4483}, {\"ngram\": \"Facebook ads\", \"from\": 4509, \"to\": 4521}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 4538, \"to\": 4540}, {\"ngram\": \"some reason\", \"from\": 4563, \"to\": 4574}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite the student protests the year before, there was a sense that this softcore, algorithmic capitalism was a new way of life, and that you might as well get on the ground floor of it.\", \"from\": 4591, \"to\": 4778, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the student\", \"from\": 4599, \"to\": 4610}, {\"ngram\": \"a sense\", \"from\": 4647, \"to\": 4654}, {\"ngram\": \"algorithmic capitalism\", \"from\": 4675, \"to\": 4697}, {\"ngram\": \"a new way\", \"from\": 4702, \"to\": 4711}, {\"ngram\": \"life\", \"from\": 4715, \"to\": 4719}, {\"ngram\": \"the ground floor\", \"from\": 4755, \"to\": 4771}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But it wasn't all forward momentum.\", \"from\": 4780, \"to\": 4815, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all forward momentum\", \"from\": 4794, \"to\": 4814}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The city was still simmering with tensions from the riots the year before, including in boroughs not miles away from the new Olympic Park.\", \"from\": 4816, \"to\": 4954, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The city\", \"from\": 4816, \"to\": 4824}, {\"ngram\": \"tensions\", \"from\": 4850, \"to\": 4858}, {\"ngram\": \"the riots\", \"from\": 4864, \"to\": 4873}, {\"ngram\": \"boroughs\", \"from\": 4904, \"to\": 4912}, {\"ngram\": \"the new Olympic Park\", \"from\": 4933, \"to\": 4953}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I was there when they reached Mare Street, and watched as teenagers climbed road signs, set bins on fire and screamed \\\"he's got a gun!\\\"\", \"from\": 4955, \"to\": 5090, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Mare Street\", \"from\": 4985, \"to\": 4996}, {\"ngram\": \"teenagers\", \"from\": 5013, \"to\": 5022}, {\"ngram\": \"road signs\", \"from\": 5031, \"to\": 5041}, {\"ngram\": \"bins\", \"from\": 5047, \"to\": 5051}, {\"ngram\": \"fire\", \"from\": 5055, \"to\": 5059}, {\"ngram\": \"a gun\", \"from\": 5083, \"to\": 5088}]}, {\"sentence\": \"into the hazy summer afternoon.\", \"from\": 5091, \"to\": 5122, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the hazy summer afternoon\", \"from\": 5096, \"to\": 5121}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The killing of Mark Duggan certainly sparked it, but clearly that cause had swept up some wider disaffection that then exploded on the streets.\", \"from\": 5123, \"to\": 5266, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5138, \"end\": 5149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shooting_of_Mark_Duggan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5759345363128987e-41, \"text\": \"Mark Duggan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shooting_of_Mark_Duggan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shooting_of_Mark_Duggan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The killing\", \"from\": 5123, \"to\": 5134}, {\"ngram\": \"that cause\", \"from\": 5184, \"to\": 5194}, {\"ngram\": \"some wider disaffection\", \"from\": 5208, \"to\": 5231}, {\"ngram\": \"the streets\", \"from\": 5254, \"to\": 5265}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The commentariat were scratching their heads as to what caused it, and when it would happen again.\", \"from\": 5267, \"to\": 5365, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The commentariat\", \"from\": 5267, \"to\": 5283}, {\"ngram\": \"their heads\", \"from\": 5300, \"to\": 5311}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The anxiety bled immediately into the Olympic summer.\", \"from\": 5367, \"to\": 5420, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The anxiety\", \"from\": 5367, \"to\": 5378}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic summer\", \"from\": 5401, \"to\": 5419}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To combat the dual threat of terrorism and/or civic unrest, the authorities decided to effectively militarise the city.\", \"from\": 5421, \"to\": 5540, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the dual threat\", \"from\": 5431, \"to\": 5446}, {\"ngram\": \"terrorism and/or civic unrest\", \"from\": 5450, \"to\": 5479}, {\"ngram\": \"the authorities\", \"from\": 5481, \"to\": 5496}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 5531, \"to\": 5539}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There were gun cops everywhere, squaddies at Overground stations and, famously, missiles installed on a tower block in Bow.\", \"from\": 5541, \"to\": 5664, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"gun cops\", \"from\": 5552, \"to\": 5560}, {\"ngram\": \"squaddies\", \"from\": 5573, \"to\": 5582}, {\"ngram\": \"Overground stations\", \"from\": 5586, \"to\": 5605}, {\"ngram\": \"famously, missiles\", \"from\": 5611, \"to\": 5629}, {\"ngram\": \"a tower block\", \"from\": 5643, \"to\": 5656}, {\"ngram\": \"Bow\", \"from\": 5660, \"to\": 5663}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I can remember being at a warehouse party in Hackney Wick in the spring of that year, and at one point the smoking area became lit up by a glaring, roving white light - the kind you may see in a UFO movie.\", \"from\": 5665, \"to\": 5870, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5710, \"end\": 5722, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hackney_Wick\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.803178487927571e-25, \"text\": \"Hackney Wick\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hackney_Wick\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hackney_Wick\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a warehouse party\", \"from\": 5689, \"to\": 5706}, {\"ngram\": \"the spring\", \"from\": 5726, \"to\": 5736}, {\"ngram\": \"that year\", \"from\": 5740, \"to\": 5749}, {\"ngram\": \"one point\", \"from\": 5758, \"to\": 5767}, {\"ngram\": \"a glaring\", \"from\": 5802, \"to\": 5811}, {\"ngram\": \"white light\", \"from\": 5820, \"to\": 5831}, {\"ngram\": \"the kind\", \"from\": 5834, \"to\": 5842}, {\"ngram\": \"a UFO movie\", \"from\": 5858, \"to\": 5869}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It turned out, it was a Royal Navy gunboat patrolling the canals, months before the event would begin.\", \"from\": 5871, \"to\": 5973, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5895, \"end\": 5905, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Royal_Navy\", \"score\": 0.9999999999745341, \"rank\": 2.5587141790638413e-11, \"text\": \"Royal Navy\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Royal_Navy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Royal_Navy\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the canals\", \"from\": 5925, \"to\": 5935}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 5951, \"to\": 5960}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Braving this foreboding yet fervent atmosphere were the \\\"gamemakers\\\", well-meaning volunteers from the rest of England who were willing to forget all the social chaos to become part of this collective experience.\", \"from\": 5975, \"to\": 6187, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6086, \"end\": 6093, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England\", \"score\": 0.9999973849260273, \"rank\": 2.4819058627714477e-06, \"text\": \"England\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this foreboding\", \"from\": 5983, \"to\": 5998}, {\"ngram\": \"fervent atmosphere\", \"from\": 6003, \"to\": 6021}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"gamemakers\", \"from\": 6027, \"to\": 6042}, {\"ngram\": \"well-meaning volunteers\", \"from\": 6045, \"to\": 6068}, {\"ngram\": \"the rest\", \"from\": 6074, \"to\": 6082}, {\"ngram\": \"all the social chaos\", \"from\": 6121, \"to\": 6141}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 6152, \"to\": 6156}, {\"ngram\": \"this collective experience\", \"from\": 6160, \"to\": 6186}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Looking back on images of them now, dancing and laughing in their purple windbreakers and polo shirts, they look very much like a volunteer security force, as if Red Nose Day and G4S had merged in some bizarre way.\", \"from\": 6188, \"to\": 6402, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"images\", \"from\": 6204, \"to\": 6210}, {\"ngram\": \"their purple windbreakers\", \"from\": 6248, \"to\": 6273}, {\"ngram\": \"polo shirts\", \"from\": 6278, \"to\": 6289}, {\"ngram\": \"a volunteer security force\", \"from\": 6316, \"to\": 6342}, {\"ngram\": \"Red Nose Day\", \"from\": 6350, \"to\": 6362}, {\"ngram\": \"G4S\", \"from\": 6367, \"to\": 6370}, {\"ngram\": \"some bizarre way\", \"from\": 6385, \"to\": 6401}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps this was one of the few times we really saw Cameron's \\\"Big Society\\\".\", \"from\": 6403, \"to\": 6479, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6455, \"end\": 6462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allison_Cameron\", \"score\": 0.9823537124311347, \"rank\": 0.01796327264317979, \"text\": \"Cameron\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allison_Cameron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allison_Cameron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the few times\", \"from\": 6427, \"to\": 6440}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ironically for the people I knew who lived within a few miles of the proceedings, it all happened at a distance.\", \"from\": 6481, \"to\": 6593, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the people\", \"from\": 6496, \"to\": 6506}, {\"ngram\": \"a few miles\", \"from\": 6531, \"to\": 6542}, {\"ngram\": \"the proceedings\", \"from\": 6546, \"to\": 6561}, {\"ngram\": \"a distance\", \"from\": 6582, \"to\": 6592}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I have a vague recollection of seeing fireworks, and witnessing Usain Bolt's record 100m in a Dalston bagel shop (and not one of the good ones).\", \"from\": 6594, \"to\": 6738, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6688, \"end\": 6695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dalston\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.78449817401589e-21, \"text\": \"Dalston\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dalston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dalston\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a vague recollection\", \"from\": 6601, \"to\": 6621}, {\"ngram\": \"fireworks\", \"from\": 6632, \"to\": 6641}, {\"ngram\": \"the good ones\", \"from\": 6723, \"to\": 6736}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What remains vivid are the personalities that were being born out of this, the obscure track and field athletes who were raised to demagogic status: Wiggins, Farah, Chris Hoy, Jessica Ennis, a young Anthony Joshua.\", \"from\": 6739, \"to\": 6953, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6897, \"end\": 6902, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prince_of_Persia\", \"score\": 0.9999999892233974, \"rank\": 1.0337994385529381e-08, \"text\": \"Farah\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prince_of_Persia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prince_of_Persia\"}, {\"begin\": 6904, \"end\": 6913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chris Hoy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\"}, {\"begin\": 6915, \"end\": 6928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Ennis-Hill\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jessica Ennis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Ennis-Hill\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Ennis-Hill\"}, {\"begin\": 6938, \"end\": 6952, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Joshua\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anthony Joshua\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Joshua\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Joshua\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the personalities\", \"from\": 6762, \"to\": 6779}, {\"ngram\": \"the obscure track and field athletes\", \"from\": 6814, \"to\": 6850}, {\"ngram\": \"demagogic status\", \"from\": 6870, \"to\": 6886}, {\"ngram\": \"Wiggins\", \"from\": 6888, \"to\": 6895}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To the press, they seemed to embody a new, \\\"better\\\" Britain.\", \"from\": 6954, \"to\": 7014, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7006, \"end\": 7013, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999978599985458, \"rank\": 2.1386970618953864e-06, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the press\", \"from\": 6957, \"to\": 6966}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But it's a Britain we have not really seen since October 2012, bar the optimistic phase of Southgatism from 2018 to 2021, and a quick flash during lockdown.\", \"from\": 7015, \"to\": 7171, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7026, \"end\": 7033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999978599985458, \"rank\": 2.1386970618953864e-06, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"October\", \"from\": 7064, \"to\": 7071}, {\"ngram\": \"the optimistic phase\", \"from\": 7082, \"to\": 7102}, {\"ngram\": \"Southgatism\", \"from\": 7106, \"to\": 7117}, {\"ngram\": \"lockdown\", \"from\": 7162, \"to\": 7170}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Time came and people forgot about the Olympics.\", \"from\": 7173, \"to\": 7220, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Time\", \"from\": 7173, \"to\": 7177}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 7187, \"to\": 7193}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 7207, \"to\": 7219}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Discussions turned to therapeutic exemption drugs and what to do with the stadia and architecture of the games.\", \"from\": 7221, \"to\": 7332, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Discussions\", \"from\": 7221, \"to\": 7232}, {\"ngram\": \"therapeutic exemption drugs\", \"from\": 7243, \"to\": 7270}, {\"ngram\": \"the stadia\", \"from\": 7291, \"to\": 7301}, {\"ngram\": \"architecture\", \"from\": 7306, \"to\": 7318}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 7322, \"to\": 7331}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There were all manner of plans mooted, and West Ham kindly gave the area some kind of sporting purpose, but walking round Stratford now, it occurs to me that the planners settled on a vision somewhere between Las Vegas and Midlands retail park.\", \"from\": 7333, \"to\": 7577, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7381, \"end\": 7384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ham\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4095152886907785e-22, \"text\": \"Ham\", \"types\": [\"Q2095\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ham\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ham\"}, {\"begin\": 7455, \"end\": 7464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stratford_station\", \"score\": 0.8155737944478726, \"rank\": 0.22613061725140882, \"text\": \"Stratford\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stratford_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stratford_station\"}, {\"begin\": 7542, \"end\": 7551, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Las_Vegas_Strip\", \"score\": 0.9523779927671313, \"rank\": 0.05000326297957381, \"text\": \"Las Vegas\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Las_Vegas_Strip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Las_Vegas_Strip\"}, {\"begin\": 7556, \"end\": 7564, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Midlands\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.173487432762863e-29, \"text\": \"Midlands\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Midlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Midlands\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"manner\", \"from\": 7348, \"to\": 7354}, {\"ngram\": \"plans\", \"from\": 7358, \"to\": 7363}, {\"ngram\": \"the area\", \"from\": 7397, \"to\": 7405}, {\"ngram\": \"some kind\", \"from\": 7406, \"to\": 7415}, {\"ngram\": \"sporting purpose\", \"from\": 7419, \"to\": 7435}, {\"ngram\": \"the planners\", \"from\": 7491, \"to\": 7503}, {\"ngram\": \"a vision\", \"from\": 7515, \"to\": 7523}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Whenever I am there, I try to make sense of it all.\", \"from\": 7578, \"to\": 7629, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sense\", \"from\": 7613, \"to\": 7618}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is an M&S that employs a legion of people to direct you to the right self-service machine, there are empty restaurants, packed shoe shops, private security units, examples of both glittering wealth and deep desperation.\", \"from\": 7630, \"to\": 7855, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7642, \"end\": 7645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marks_&_Spencer\", \"score\": 0.9993870436348763, \"rank\": 0.0006133323111129803, \"text\": \"M&S\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marks_&_Spencer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marks_&_Spencer\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a legion\", \"from\": 7659, \"to\": 7667}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 7671, \"to\": 7677}, {\"ngram\": \"the right self-service machine\", \"from\": 7695, \"to\": 7725}, {\"ngram\": \"empty restaurants\", \"from\": 7737, \"to\": 7754}, {\"ngram\": \"packed shoe shops\", \"from\": 7756, \"to\": 7773}, {\"ngram\": \"private security units\", \"from\": 7775, \"to\": 7797}, {\"ngram\": \"examples\", \"from\": 7799, \"to\": 7807}, {\"ngram\": \"both glittering wealth\", \"from\": 7811, \"to\": 7833}, {\"ngram\": \"deep desperation\", \"from\": 7838, \"to\": 7854}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All played out in a landscape of luxury apartment blocks and council-mandated green space.\", \"from\": 7856, \"to\": 7946, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a landscape\", \"from\": 7874, \"to\": 7885}, {\"ngram\": \"luxury apartment blocks\", \"from\": 7889, \"to\": 7912}, {\"ngram\": \"council-mandated green space\", \"from\": 7917, \"to\": 7945}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The real Stratford exists somewhere in the beyond.\", \"from\": 7947, \"to\": 7997, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7956, \"end\": 7965, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stratford_station\", \"score\": 0.8155737944478726, \"rank\": 0.22613061725140882, \"text\": \"Stratford\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stratford_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stratford_station\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the beyond\", \"from\": 7986, \"to\": 7996}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And I think, in some ways, this is the real Olympic legacy.\", \"from\": 7999, \"to\": 8058, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some ways\", \"from\": 8015, \"to\": 8024}, {\"ngram\": \"the real Olympic legacy\", \"from\": 8034, \"to\": 8057}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was the moment where even a place as rough-edged as Stratford became conquerable.\", \"from\": 8059, \"to\": 8143, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8114, \"end\": 8123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stratford_station\", \"score\": 0.8155737944478726, \"rank\": 0.22613061725140882, \"text\": \"Stratford\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stratford_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stratford_station\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the moment\", \"from\": 8066, \"to\": 8076}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since the Olympic torch passed through those dark streets of old London, there have been skyscrapers hastily-erected in Acton, chain hotels in Canning Town, a \\\"tech city\\\" in Croydon.\", \"from\": 8144, \"to\": 8326, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8209, \"end\": 8215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999979099812, \"rank\": 2.0903602504530897e-09, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 8264, \"end\": 8269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Municipal_Borough_of_Acton\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.361329264323186e-29, \"text\": \"Acton\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Municipal_Borough_of_Acton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Municipal_Borough_of_Acton\"}, {\"begin\": 8318, \"end\": 8325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Croydon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3355664654234853e-19, \"text\": \"Croydon\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Croydon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Croydon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic torch\", \"from\": 8150, \"to\": 8167}, {\"ngram\": \"those dark streets\", \"from\": 8183, \"to\": 8201}, {\"ngram\": \"skyscrapers\", \"from\": 8233, \"to\": 8244}, {\"ngram\": \"chain hotels\", \"from\": 8271, \"to\": 8283}, {\"ngram\": \"Canning Town\", \"from\": 8287, \"to\": 8299}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"tech city\", \"from\": 8301, \"to\": 8313}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Almost as if the whole city was put on the market, or under the spotlight of globalisation.\", \"from\": 8327, \"to\": 8418, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the whole city\", \"from\": 8340, \"to\": 8354}, {\"ngram\": \"the market\", \"from\": 8366, \"to\": 8376}, {\"ngram\": \"the spotlight\", \"from\": 8387, \"to\": 8400}, {\"ngram\": \"globalisation\", \"from\": 8404, \"to\": 8417}]}, {\"sentence\": \"How that impacts Paris - a city with even more bad feeling than London in 2012 - remains to be seen.\", \"from\": 8420, \